==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Signal to noise
<hw>Sig"nal to
noise"</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Electronics,
Information science, Experimental science)</fld> <def>The ratio of the
intensity of a signal{2} to the background noise detected by a measuring
instrument, especially in a communications channel; the higher the
ratio, the more accurately the information contained can be interpreted.
The term is applied not only to human communications, but to the
detection of information in any system that is being studied to gain
knowledge; <as>as, the <ex>signal-to-noise ratio</ex> of light signals
in older optic fibers drops to an unusable level after several
miles.</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Signal</ent>⟦br⟧
